<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,769,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,769,793]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Comments.</emphasis>
The diagnosis is based primarily on 
<collectingRegion box="[789,879,770,794]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Florida</collectingRegion>
specimens. The 
<collectingRegion box="[1079,1224,770,794]" country="Bahamas" name="Long Island" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Long Island</collectingRegion>
specimen is worn and bears only faint markings. The left valve saccular process is somewhat variable but within the range of variation seen in 
<collectingRegion box="[523,613,834,858]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Florida</collectingRegion>
specimens. In 
<collectingRegion box="[802,895,834,858]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Florida</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter" authorityName="Walter" box="[909,1235,834,858]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Eupatorium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="compositifolium">
<emphasis box="[909,1141,834,858]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E. compositifolium</emphasis>
Walter
</taxonomicName>
is an occasional host and additional hosts are used in the western states (
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; T. A. Lott" box="[897,1205,865,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref7548" refString="Matthews, D. L., and T. A. Lott. 2005. Larval hostplants of the Pterophoridae (Lepidoptera: Pterophoroidea). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 76: 1 - 324." type="journal article" year="2005">Matthews and Lott 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
